---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
import Markdown from '../../../Markdown.astro';
import AIBalloon from '../../AIBalloon.astro';
import AIBalloonMessage from '../../AIBalloonMessage.astro';
import AIResponseMessage from '../../AIResponseMessage.astro';
import HighlightBox from '../../HighlightBox.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Use Plain Language and Concrete Examples"
  description="Avoid technical jargon and abstract concepts. Use everyday language and specific examples that users can relate to."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={320} label="Plain language explanations" toggle>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full max-w-9600">
      <AIBalloon>
        <AIBalloonMessage>Translate into Italian: It’s raining cats and dogs.</AIBalloonMessage>
      </AIBalloon>
      <AIResponseMessage>
        <HighlightBox label="Real use" variant="success">
          <Markdown
            typography="detail"
            content={`
This is an idiom, so it shouldn’t be translated literally. It means that it’s raining very heavily.

A natural Italian translation would be:

"Piove a dirotto."

For example:

"I can’t go out, it’s raining cats and dogs" → "Non posso uscire, piove a dirotto."
        `}
          />
        </HighlightBox>
      </AIResponseMessage>
    </div>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full max-w-9600">
      <AIBalloon>
        <AIBalloonMessage>Translate into Italian: It’s raining cats and dogs.</AIBalloonMessage>
      </AIBalloon>
      <AIResponseMessage>
        <HighlightBox label="Unuseful explanation" variant="error">
          <Markdown
            typography="detail"
            content={`
This expression is a non-compositional idiomatic construct characterized by semantic opacity, where the literal lexical units do not correspond to the intended figurative meaning. The appropriate Italian equivalent involves a culturally adapted meteorological intensifier.
        `}
          />
        </HighlightBox>
      </AIResponseMessage>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Use everyday language and specific examples that users can relate to.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Use technical jargon, acronyms, or abstract concepts without explanation.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Show concrete examples of what the AI output means in practice.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">Assume users understand technical terms or AI/ML concepts.</UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
